<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,152,395]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,260,287]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Comments.</emphasis>
Besides the 
<typeStatus box="[477,580,261,287]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">lectotype</typeStatus>
and the 
<typeStatus box="[674,828,261,287]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">paralectotype</typeStatus>
, no more specimens are known, so their variation cannot be documented; besides the status of the type specimens was reviewed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Paris, M." box="[1015,1155,297,323]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="143 - 264" refId="ref32882" refString="Paris, M. (1994) Catalogo de tipos de ortopteroides (Insecta) de Ignacio Bolivar, I: Blattaria, Mantodea, Phasmoptera y Orthoptera (Stenopelmatoidea, Rhaphidophoroidea, Tettigonioidea, Grylloidea, Tetrigoidea). Eos, Revista espanola de Entomologia, 69, 143 - 264." type="journal article" year="1994">Paris (1994)</bibRefCitation>
. Historically, this species has been mistaken with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1909" box="[431,580,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis box="[431,580,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see differences in the key to species) (Westerdujin &amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. &amp; Monzon-Sierra, J." pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="379 - 411" refId="ref30630" refString="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. &amp; Monzon-Sierra, J. (2014) Studies in Guatemalan Caelifera: New grasshoppers and monkey grasshoppers (Orthoptera: Caelifera: Acridoidea &amp; Eumastacoidea) and an updated checklist. Zootaxa, 3857 (3), 379 - 411. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3857.3.3" type="journal article" year="2014">Cadena-Castañeda, 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Huaman, L. &amp; Westerduijn, R. &amp; Cadena-Castaneda, O. J." box="[222,448,369,395]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref32076" refString="Huaman, L., Westerduijn, R. &amp; Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. (2014) Common Orthoptera from Tingo Maria, Huanuco-Peru. Field Museum Guides, 1 - 6. Available from: https: // fieldguides. fieldmuseum. org / sites / default / files / rapid-color-guides-pdfs / 605 % 20 Tingo % 20 Maria % 20 Orthops % 20 b 1. pdf (accessed 2 September 2019)" type="book chapter" year="2014">
Huamán 
<emphasis box="[324,373,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al</emphasis>
, 2014
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
